Press Releases.Title: 262 New Cases of Covid-19 Infection
Press Releases.MainContent:
As of 21 June 2020, 12pm, the Ministry of Health (MOH) has preliminarilyconfirmed an additional 262 cases of COVID-19 infection in Singapore, the vastmajority of whom are Work Permit holders residing in foreign worker dormitories.Based on our investigations so far, there are 9 cases in the community, of whom 3are Singaporeans/Permanent Residents and 6 are Work Pass holders.

2.  We are still working through the details of the cases, and further updates willbe shared via the MOH press release that will be issued tonight.

MINISTRY OF HEALTH
21 JUNE 2020
